RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 53. Maiden Claiming Purse 8000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILEY'S WONDER came out and bumped with rival on hind end, tracked dueling leaders along the inside on the backstretch, continued well place on the turn, inherited lead when rival blew the turn and floated out other dueling rival, kept to task in the lane and held off game rival to the wire. ABBEY OOPS vied for lead along the rail, continued along the rail on the turn, began to float out midway through turn and ended up in the five path, despite the trouble, came back and kept on in a game effort. HOP ON AND RIDE off slow and bumped by rival at the start, settled well off the pace and off the rail on the backstretch, continued off the rail on the turn, launched a mild bid along the rail to get up for third. BOLD TALKER came in and bumped TOUGH TO CATCH, causing rival to clip heels and lose the rider, tracked duo after that fiasco, continued two wide on the turn and into the lane, asked and was in contention the the sixteenth pole where he began to weaken. HAMPTONRUN broke in and bumped rival at the start, vied for lead two wide on the backstretch, continued vying for lead into the turn, floated out by rival midway through the turn, dropped back and went three wide rest of turn, and failed to respond in the lane. TOUGH TO CATCH outside rival came in and inside rival came out and bumped TOUGH TO CATCH, and in the process, clipped heels, stumbling and losing the rider at the start. STEWARDS INQUIRY, AFTER REVIEW BOLD TALKER WAS DISQUALIFED AND UNPLACED FOR COMING IN AND CAUSING TOUGH TO CATCH TO LOSE RIDER AT THE START

RACE.FOOTNOTES: POLLO D'ORO pressed pace two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, battled heading into the lane, all out to wire and got up late. CHASING THE VISION went to lead in between rivals on the backstretch, went to rail heading into the turn, continued to lead on the turn, held a narrow advantage heading into the lane, dug in under urging and nailed in the last couple jumps. HOLYJAZZ pressed pace early, tried to hold rail but had to cede the rail, continued to chased along the inside on the turn, a tad in tight heading into the lane, found room and kept on while unable to catch leaders. MISSING MAURICE bit slow and dropped back at the start, settled off the pace along the inside, continued along the inside on the turn, entered lane in the rear, and responded mildly in between to improve. DIVINELY DIVERSE tracked pace two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, launched a seemingly promising four wide bid at the top of the lane but flattened out mid stretch. HELICOPTER PILOT tracked pace three wide on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn, and failed to kick on when outfinished in the lane.
